title: E-conomics
text: How to order integration Customer contacts Support regarding integration for E-conomics The integration costs DKR 4900,- pr store. Try not to inform of prices and let CSM deal with it. Step1: Customer Support creates a ticket in CRM. Keep the ticket open with Owner: DdD Integrations and status: Passed to Consultancy Example template for description: Name: Trine Store: Esprit GroupID: 235 Can you please provide template for e-conomics integrations? It's for following ClientIDs: 235006, 235008 Step2: Customer Support contacts Customer Success Manager (CSM, Cem Arslan) Step3: Customer Support receives email/Order from CSM Step4: Change ticket status to Passed to Development Step5: Ticket is changed back to Passed to Consultancy by development and includes a excel file looking like this: Step 6: Send the files via email to the customer or accountant, along with "E-conomic Velkomstbrev" Step 7: Customer/Accountant returns the files along with AgreementGrantToken and name of the draft in E-conomics. Step 8: Update the ticket with the received files, AgreementGrantToken, Draftname and which date we should send the data from like below. Step 9: Change status to Passed to Development Step 10: Customer support receives confirmation that it's done and data is set up to run automatically; Inform the customer. Step 11: Close the ticket
description:
How to order integration 

  

  

Customer contacts Support regarding integration for E-conomics 

  

The integration costs DKR 4900,- pr store. Try not to inform of prices and let CSM deal with it. 

  

  

Step1: Customer Support creates a ticket in CRM. 

  

Keep the ticket open with Owner: DdD Integrations and status: Passed to Consultancy 

  

Example template for description:  

  

Name: Trine 

Store: Esprit 

GroupID: 235 

  

Can you please provide template for e-conomics integrations? 

It's for following ClientIDs: 235006, 235008 

  

  

Step2: Customer Support contacts Customer Success Manager (CSM, Cem Arslan) 

Step3: Customer Support receives email/Order from CSM  

Step4: Change ticket status to Passed to Development 

Step5: Ticket is changed back to Passed to Consultancy by development and includes a excel file looking like this:  


 

Step 6: Send the files via email to the customer or accountant, along with "E-conomic Velkomstbrev" 

Step 7: Customer/Accountant returns the files along with AgreementGrantToken and name of the draft in E-conomics. 

Step 8: Update the ticket with the received files, AgreementGrantToken, Draftname and which date we should send the data from like below. 

Step 9: Change status to Passed to Development

Step 10: Customer support receives confirmation that it's done and data is set up to run automatically; Inform the customer. 

Step 11: Close the ticket

title: Missing data in E-conomics integration
text: Customer calls and informs they are missing data in E-conomics from a certain date. Step1: Create a case for DdD Backoffice Template: Name: John Phone: +4540815663 Store: Oldager Sko, Amager ClientID: 161001 Customer is missing all data in e-conomics on 30.11-2022. Can you resend data please? Make sure you have all clientIDs and missing dates if it's for multiple stores in the same group. Be specific! Step 2: Change ticket status to Passed to Development Step 3: Ticket is Passed to Consultancy with confirmation that data is resent. Usually this takes 15-30 minutes and the data can be seen in E-conomics. Step 4: Inform customer and close the ticket.
description:
Customer calls and informs they are missing data in E-conomics from a certain date. 

  

  

Step1: Create a case for DdD Backoffice 

  

Template: 

  

Name: John 

Phone: +4540815663 

Store: Oldager Sko, Amager 

ClientID: 161001 

  

Customer is missing all data in e-conomics on 30.11-2022.  

Can you resend data please? 

  

Make sure you have all clientIDs and missing dates if it's for multiple stores in the same group. 

Be specific! 

Step 2: Change ticket status to Passed to Development 


Step 3: Ticket is Passed to Consultancy with confirmation that data is resent. 

Usually this takes 15-30 minutes and the data can be seen in E-conomics. 


Step 4: Inform customer and close the ticket.

title: GoFact
text: ustomer contacts Support regarding integration for GoFact The integration costs DKR 4900,- pr store. Try not to inform of prices and let CSM deal with it. GoFact is an integrator for Budgets / finance - They are the integrators. GoFact uses a Group Token so whenever a new store is added to a group, you don't need to order a new API key, they can add to the same GroupToken. Step1: Customer Support creates a ticket in CRM. Keep the ticket open with Owner: DdD Integrations and status: Passed to Development Example template for description: Name: Trine Store: Esprit GroupID: 235 Can you please provide API key for GoFact integration It's for following ClientIDs: 235006, 235008 Step2: When ticket comes back from DdD Integrations, forward the API key to GoFact at Support@gofact.net - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Example:

ustomer contacts Support regarding integration for GoFact


The integration costs DKR 4900,- pr store. Try not to inform of prices and let CSM deal with it.

    It's for following ClientIDs: 235006, 235008

title: Miinto
text: Customer contacts Support regarding integration for Miinto webshop. The integration costs DKR 4900,- pr store. Try not to inform of prices and let CSM deal with it. Never send API key to the customer directly, only send to integrator! Step 1: Customer Support creates a ticket in CRM. Keep the ticket open with Owner: DdD Integrations and status: Passed to Consultancy Example template for description: Name: Mikael Bertelsen Phone: +45 40 16 86 86 Store: Room 1006 ClientID: 206001 Integrator: Kundeservice@miinto.dk Can you please create webshop and provide API token for Miinto? Mark all items currently in stock for webshop Mark all items with transactions in the last 2 years Step 2: Customer Support contacts Customer Success Manager (CSM, Cem Arslan) Step 3: Customer Support receives email/Order from CSM Step 4: Change ticket status to Passed to Development Step 5: Ticket is changed back to Passed to Consultancy by development and includes an API key and confirmation that it's created. Step 6: Send the GroupToken and WebshopToken to the Integrator Step 7: Close ticket
description:
Customer contacts Support regarding integration for Miinto webshop. 

  

The integration costs DKR 4900,- pr store. Try not to inform of prices and let CSM deal with it. 

  

Never send API key to the customer directly, only send to integrator! 

  

  

Step 1: Customer Support creates a ticket in CRM. 

  

Keep the ticket open with Owner: DdD Integrations and status: Passed to Consultancy 

  

Example template for description:  

  

Name: Mikael Bertelsen 

Phone: +45 40 16 86 86 

Store: Room 1006 

ClientID: 206001 

  

Integrator: Kundeservice@miinto.dk 

  

Can you please create webshop and provide API token for Miinto? 

Mark all items currently in stock for webshop 

Mark all items with transactions in the last 2 years 

  

  

Step 2: Customer Support contacts Customer Success Manager (CSM, Cem Arslan) 

Step 3: Customer Support receives email/Order from CSM 

Step 4: Change ticket status to Passed to Development 

Step 5: Ticket is changed back to Passed to Consultancy by development and includes an API key and confirmation that it's created. 


 



  

Step 6: Send the GroupToken and WebshopToken to the Integrator

title: Missing data Navision integration
text: Customer calls informing they are missing data in Navision / C5. For Navision they are missing the daily Kasse.dat files. Step1: Create a case for DdD Backoffice Template: Name: John Phone: +45 1223 3445 Store: Shopshoppen GroupID: 123 Customer is missing kasse.dat on 30.11-2022 on clientIDs: 123001 Can you please resend? Make sure you have all clientIDs and missing dates if it's for multiple stores in the same group. Be specific! Step 2: Change ticket status to Passed to Development Step 3: Ticket is Passed to Consultancy with confirmation that data is resent. Data is available after 09:00 AM or 15:00 PM Step 4: Inform customer and close the ticket.

title: Shopify
text: Customer contacts Support regarding integration for Shopify webshop. The integration costs DKR 4900,- pr store. Try not to inform of prices and let CSM deal with it. Never send API key to the customer directly, only send to integrator! Shopify doesn't do the Integration themselves, it has to be done by 3rd party - Usually this is IEX. Step 1: Customer Support creates a ticket in CRM. Keep the ticket open with Owner: DdD Integrations and status: Passed to Consultancy Example template for description: Name: Mikael Bertelsen Phone: +45 40 16 86 86 Store: Room 1006 ClientID: 206001 Integrator: support@iex.dk Can you please create webshop and provide API token for Shopify? Mark all items currently in stock for webshop Mark all items with transactions in the last 2 years Step 2: Customer Support contacts Customer Success Manager (CSM, Cem Arslan) Step 3: Customer Support receives email/Order from CSM Step 4: Change ticket status to Passed to Development Step 5: Ticket is changed back to Passed to Consultancy by development and includes an API key and confirmation that it's created. Step 6: Send the GroupToken and WebshopToken to the Integrator (IEX) Step 7: Close ticket
